This paper deals with the management and exchange of graph data, which is a common topic in several subfields of computer science. The most likely category is cs.DB (Databases), as the paper proposes a new model for managing graph data and discusses interoperability between different database implementations. The paper also touches on topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), such as graph-based machine learning and knowledge representation. Additionally, the paper proposes a new serialization format for graph data, which is relevant to data structures (cs.DS) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the practical implementation of the proposed model and serialization, which falls under software engineering (cs.SE).
